BITRA Chatbot is an AI-powered virtual assistant developed for Bannari Amman Institute of Technology.
It serves students, faculty, and researchers by providing instant access to academic and research information.
The chatbot answers queries about courses, projects, research papers, and publications.
It provides updates on workshops, seminars, and conferences organized by the institute.
Students can get guidance on journal selection, grant applications, and patent filing.
Faculty members can share research updates and connect with students through the chatbot.
BITRA Chatbot uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) to understand and respond accurately.
It tracks research deadlines, submissions, and important academic notifications.
The chatbot acts as a 24/7 assistant for research guidance and academic support.
It helps reduce manual workload by automating routine queries and responses.
BITRA Chatbot encourages collaboration between students, faculty, and industry experts.
It provides recommendations for innovative project ideas and research directions.
The system learns from interactions to improve response accuracy over time.
BITRA Chatbot promotes digital literacy and efficient use of research resources.
Overall, it enhances learning, research productivity, and academic excellence at BIT.
